# Title case (default)

Unless the user gives different instructions, write **user-facing text in title case**: capitalize the first letter of **each word** in a sentence or phrase.

Applies to:

- i18n strings in `locales/`
- Button, label, heading, menu, and toast copy
- Empty states, errors, and success messages shown in the UI

Examples:

- ✅ `Your Email Is Not Verified`
- ✅ `Save Password`
- ❌ `Your email is not verified`
- ❌ `Save password`

**Code:** toast/feedback messages go through `notify.*()` in `lib/frontend/feedback/notify.ts`, which applies `capitalizeFeedbackText()` from `lib/frontend/feedback/format.ts`. When adding new i18n keys or static UI strings, author them in title case at the source.

Sentence case or lowercase is fine only when the user explicitly asks for it, or when matching an external API message verbatim.
